gomodel:SYNGO_683  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: * Triad3A/RNF216 is an E3 ubiquitin ligase targeting Arc-an activity-regulated gene product that regulates AMPA receptor endocytosis and synaptic plasticity.\n*By limiting Arc protein levels induced by synaptic activity, Triad3A regulates Arc-dependent forms of synaptic plasticity.\n* Clathrin-Localized Triad3A Controls GluA1 AMPAR Endocytosis (Fig 6)\n* Triad3A Is Required for Activity- Induced Upscaling of Synaptic Strength (Fig 7). Experimental description: Supp info: Hippocampal neurons were isolated from E18 RAT embryos and cultured as previously described (Ehlers, 2000).\nHomeostatic scaling and baseline mEPSC recordings (Fig 7). Whole-cell voltage clamp recordings were performed on DIV 17-21 hippocampal neurons cultured at high density on poly-D-lysine coated glass coverslips. Species not stated but presumably rat (see above).\nDHPG-induced synaptic depression (Fig 8). Hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from postnatal day 0 pups from C57BL/6 wild type MICE as described previously (Canal et al., 2011)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_683" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

